Class FeatureCollectionDataAdapter

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AttachedIteratorDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, ModelConvertingDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, Persistable, DataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, IndexDependentDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, WritableDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, DataReader<Object>, DataWriter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection,Object>

    public class FeatureCollectionDataAdapter
extends AbstractDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>
implements IndexDependentDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>, ModelConvertingDataAdapter<org.geotools.feature.DefaultFeatureCollection>
    This data adapter will handle all reading/writing concerns for storing and retrieving GeoTools FeatureCollection objects to and from a GeoWave persistent store in Accumulo. Note that if the implementor needs to write rows with particular visibility, that must be done by providing a FieldVisibilityHandler to this constructor. The adapter will use the SimpleFeature's default geometry for spatial indexing and will use either the first temporal attribute (a Calendar or Date object) as the timestamp of a temporal index or if there are multiple temporal attributes and one contains the term 'start' and the other contains either the term 'stop' or 'end' it will interpret the combination of these attributes as a time range to index on.
